21/08/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Boris Trajkovski and Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski decided on Wednesday (20 August) that the country should have a military brigade for special operations. The leaders met with top army officers and agreed that a concrete proposal on the structure and financing of the brigade should be drafted in two weeks. According to press reports, the brigade would include about 1,400 elite army professionals. NATO has recommended the establishment of such a structure as part of integration preparations. (Utrinski Vesnik - 21/08/03; MIA, Makfax - 20/08/03)
